@startuml
title Workflow Slots Overview (S1-S8)

left to right direction
hide empty description
skinparam DefaultFontName Arial
skinparam Shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #444444
skinparam PackageStyle rectangle
skinparam package {
  BackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  BorderColor #94A3B8
  FontColor #0F172A
}
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F4F6F8
  BorderColor #5A6473
  FontColor #111827
  RoundCorner 8
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF7D6
  BorderColor #C9A227
  FontColor #3F3F46
}

rectangle "Profile resolver\nWorkflowProfileResolver" as Resolver
rectangle "Transition catalog and\nruntime workflow engine" as Engine

note as ResolutionRules
Slot resolution rules
1. Match active profile by hospital/site/department fallback.
2. Pick highest-priority rule for the slot.
3. Rule must be enabled and effective now.
4. Deserialize and validate config JSON.
5. If no valid rule exists, use built-in fallback defaults.

Important:
Disabling a slot rule does not remove a workflow phase.
It removes that configuration override for the slot.
Runtime then falls back to defaults or another matching rule.
end note

ResolutionRules .. Resolver

Resolver --> Engine : resolved slot config

package "Phase 2-4: Imaging, Contouring, Review" {
  rectangle "S1\nContouring Strategy\nCode: S1_CONTOURING_STRATEGY\nPurpose: auto contour provider and fallback behavior\nAffects: contour provider, auto-contour monitoring,\nauto-forward-to-Monaco, manual contour fallback\nIf disabled or unmatched: fallback S1 defaults apply\nDefault effect: AutoContourEnabled=false, Provider=PvMed,\nAutoForwardToMonaco=false, AllowManualForward=true,\nManualWorkItemRole=Doctor" as S1

  rectangle "S2\nContour Review Policy\nCode: S2_CONTOUR_REVIEW_POLICY\nPurpose: review mode, rejection behavior, timeout\nAffects: review expectations and contour rework routing\nIf disabled or unmatched: fallback S2 defaults apply\nDefault effect: single review, contour rework target\nremains enabled, Doctor handles rework" as S2
}

package "Phase 5: Planning" {
  rectangle "S3\nPlan Dispatch\nCode: S3_PLAN_DISPATCH\nPurpose: assignment mode and escalation policy\nAffects: planning target role and dispatch behavior\nIf disabled or unmatched: fallback S3 defaults apply\nDefault effect: AutoAssignByRole, target role Dosimetrist" as S3
}

package "Phase 6-7: Re-review and QA" {
  rectangle "S4\nPlan Re-review Policy\nCode: S4_PLAN_REREVIEW_POLICY\nPurpose: optional re-review trigger and reviewer role\nAffects: whether re-review is enabled and who reviews\nIf disabled or unmatched: fallback S4 defaults apply\nDefault effect: Enabled=false, reviewer role SeniorPhysicist" as S4

  rectangle "S5\nPlan Double Check\nCode: S5_PLAN_DOUBLE_CHECK\nPurpose: optional independent double-check policy\nAffects: whether double-check is enabled and who performs it\nIf disabled or unmatched: fallback S5 defaults apply\nDefault effect: Enabled=false, work item role QAReviewer" as S5
}

package "Phase 8-9: Scheduling, Treatment, Completion" {
  rectangle "S6\nQueue and Cancel Policy\nCode: S6_QUEUE_AND_CANCEL_POLICY\nPurpose: queue mode and cancellation constraints\nAffects: queue handling, cancel window, cancel final status\nIf disabled or unmatched: fallback S6 defaults apply\nDefault effect: QueueMode=MsqDriven, AllowCancel=true,\nCancelAllowedBeforeStatus=Treating" as S6

  rectangle "S7\nTreatment Completion Policy\nCode: S7_TREATMENT_COMPLETION_POLICY\nPurpose: completion mode and mismatch handling\nAffects: how completion is decided and mismatch escalation\nIf disabled or unmatched: fallback S7 defaults apply\nDefault effect: ByCourseCompletedEvent, mismatch creates\nexception work item for Therapist" as S7

  rectangle "S8\nException Handling Policy\nCode: S8_EXCEPTION_HANDLING_POLICY\nPurpose: retry strategy, fallback work item, notifications\nAffects: retry/backoff behavior and manual exception handling\nIf disabled or unmatched: fallback S8 defaults apply\nDefault effect: retries enabled, manual fallback enabled,\nexception work item type TreatmentExceptionHandling" as S8
}

Engine --> S1 : contouring decisions
Engine --> S2 : contour review decisions
Engine --> S3 : planning dispatch decisions
Engine --> S4 : re-review decisions
Engine --> S5 : double-check decisions
Engine --> S6 : queue and cancel decisions
Engine --> S7 : treatment completion decisions
Engine --> S8 : exception handling decisions

S1 --> S2
S2 --> S3
S3 --> S4
S4 --> S5
S5 --> S6
S6 --> S7
S7 --> S8

note bottom of S1
Concrete example
If an S1 rule is disabled, the resolver ignores it.
If no other enabled S1 rule matches, fallback defaults are used.
That means contouring is not skipped.
Instead, runtime falls back to manual-first behavior:
- no auto-contour dispatch
- no auto-forward to Monaco
- manual contour fallback stays available
end note

legend right
== Meaning of disabled ==
Disabled rule:
- not selected by resolver
- does not delete the phase
- may expose fallback defaults
- may allow another matching rule to win

== Practical reading ==
Use the slot to tune behavior inside a phase,
not to remove the phase from the workflow.
endlegend

@enduml
